The police say they’ve opened an inquest following the death of five family members in a shack fire at the Lusaka Informal Settlement in Mamelodi. JOHANNESBURG - The police say they’ve opened an inquest following the death of five family members in a shack fire at the Lusaka Informal Settlement in Mamelodi. The incident took place in the early hours of Saturday morning when the victims were asleep. An exploded gas cylinder was found in the wreckage after the fire was extinguished. The police say the victims were burnt beyond recognition and investigations into the cause of the blaze are continuing. The police’s Kay Makhubele said: “At the moment, we don’t know what caused the fire and appeal to anyone with information that might assist us to come forward.”